# Text-to-Image Generation using Stable Diffusion

## Introduction
This project demonstrates how a pre-trained text-to-image model can generate images from textual descriptions. The model used is Stable Diffusion, which is capable of producing high-quality images.

## Objective
To generate domain-specific images (such as anime, medical, or flowers) using a pre-trained model and custom prompts.

## Tools & Technologies
- Python
- Stable Diffusion
- Diffusers Library
- PyTorch
- Kaggle (GPU)

## Methodology
1. Enabled GPU in Kaggle
2. Loaded pre-trained Stable Diffusion model
3. Generated images using custom text prompts
4. Saved and downloaded output image

## Sample Prompt
"anime girl with pink hair, ultra detailed, 4k, cinematic lighting"

